# NailsByKate Website Project Rules

## Project Overview

This is a Next.js website for a nail salon called "Nails by Kate". The website includes sections for pricing, booking, about, and gallery.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js with TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- React components

## Code Style Preferences

- Use TypeScript for all components
- Use functional components with arrow functions
- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling
- Prefer semantic HTML elements
- Use Norwegian text for content (PRISLISTE, BOOKING, OM MEG, GALLERY)

## File Structure

- Components in `src/components/`
- Pages follow Next.js app router structure
- Use `.tsx` extension for React components

## Navigation Requirements

- Navigation should link to sections using anchor links (#prisliste, #booking, etc.)
- Include horizontal rules (hr) between navigation items
- Mobile-responsive design

## Styling Guidelines

- Use Flexbox for layouts
- Maintain clean, professional salon aesthetic
- Ensure responsive design for mobile devices

## When making changes:

- Always use proper TypeScript types
- Follow existing naming conventions
- Test navigation functionality
- Maintain Norwegian language for UI text
